    "text": "BACE1 inhibitor toxicity stems from disruption of essential non-amyloid substrates rather than from on-target amyloid reduction itself. Predictions: Substrate-selective BACE1 inhibitors that spare non-APP substrates (e.g., neuregulin-1, CHL1) will show reduced cognitive and synaptic side effects in trials.; Conditional BACE1 knockouts limited to APP processing will not reproduce the cognitive worsening seen in broad inhibitor trials.",
